1. Aspect

ğŸ‘‰ A class that contains cross-cutting logic
@Aspect
@Component
public class LoggingAspect { }

2. Advice
ğŸ‘‰ When the code should run
Types:
@Before
@After
@AfterReturning
@AfterThrowing
@Around

3. Join Point
ğŸ‘‰ Where advice executes
(Method execution, exception, return)

4. Pointcut
ğŸ‘‰ Which methods should be intercepted
execution(* SB.AOP.Empdata.*(..))

5. Target Object
ğŸ‘‰ The actual business class (Empdata)

6. Proxy
ğŸ‘‰ A wrapper object created by Spring
(all AOP happens via proxy)

âš ï¸ No proxy = no AOP

4ï¸âƒ£ How AOP works internally (MUST KNOW)
Spring starts
Scans beans
Finds @Aspect
Creates proxy object
Calls proxy instead of real object
Advice runs â†’ then method executes
